| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/index.ts` | Lines 53-55 | Entry point routing to `acp` command |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/commands/acp.ts` | Lines 11-12, 35-66 | Command handler, parses args, calls manager |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/utils/acp-server-manager.ts` | Lines 27, 101-104 | Spawns `trae-cli acp serve` |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/utils/acp-server-manager.ts` | Lines 108-123 | Port detection regex patterns |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/utils/acp-server-manager.ts` | Lines 146-152 | Exit handler (where your error originates) |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/utils/acp-server-manager.ts` | Lines 154-167 | 15-second timeout logic |
| `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/src/utils/acp-client.ts` | Lines 36-147 | HTTP client that connects to detected port |

---

### Diagnostic Recommendation

The error "ACP server exited before port detected" means the `trae-cli` process closed **before any of the port regex patterns matched**. To debug this, you could:

1. Run `trae-cli acp serve` manually in a terminal to see its exact output format
2. Check if it outputs something like `Server running on http://127.0.0.1:PORT` which would NOT match the current patterns (since they look for `localhost`, not `127.0.0.1`)
3. Look at the diagnostic trace that is included in the error message (the `buildDiagnostic()` function at lines 63-71 logs all startup events)
